To automate the selection of all checkboxes on a page and save them with a click,
We'll dance through the DOM, like shadows on the wall.
First, let's gather our tools: a script to wield,
And perhaps some CSS to style, for elegance and yield.

```javascript
document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", function() {
    // Select all checkboxes on the page
    var checkboxes = document.querySelectorAll('input[type="checkbox"]');

    // Function to check or uncheck all
    function toggleCheckboxes() {
        checkboxes.forEach(function(checkbox) {
            checkbox.checked = !checkbox.checked; // Flip their state
        });
    }

    // Find the Save button and add an event listener
    var saveButton = document.querySelector('button[type="submit"], button[aria-label="Save"]');
    if (saveButton) {
        saveButton.addEventListener("click", toggleCheckboxes);
    }
});
```

This script waits for the page to load, then selects all checkboxes.
It flips their states, and attaches an event to the Save button's click.
When you tap that button, all checkboxes will change their minds,
A seamless dance of form elements, under your command's design.

